The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks for histopathology diagnosis, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of semi-supervised learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The examination process of lymph nodes involves analyzing images, which can also fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of metrics to evaluate the performance of the model, which can also fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
